DOCUMENT();

############################################################
# Load Macros
############################################################
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
  "PGlateximage.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "parserNumberWithUnits.pl",
  "contextForm.pl",
  "Pd.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);
COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');

############################################################
# Header
############################################################
TEXT(beginproblem());

############################################################
# PG Setup Code
############################################################
Context('Numeric');
($h,$w) = num_sort((8..20)[NchooseK(13,2)]);
$hU = NumberWithUnits("$h ft");
$wU = NumberWithUnits("$w ft");
$s = random(1,2,1)+random(0.1,0.9,0.1);
$sU = NumberWithUnits("$s ft");
$area = int(($h+2*$s)*($w+2*$s) - $h*$w);
$areaU = NumberWithUnits("$area ft^2");
$a = 4;
$b = 2*($h+$w);
$c = -$area;
$surface = Formula("4x^2 + $b x")->reduce;
$f = Formula("4x^2 + $b x + $c")->reduce;
$negb = -$b;
$bsquared = $b*$b;
$discriminant = $bsquared - 4*$a*$c;
$sqrtdisc = Real(sqrt($discriminant));
$a2 = 2*$a;
$r = ($negb - $sqrtdisc)/$a2;
$s = ($negb + $sqrtdisc)/$a2;
$sU = NumberWithUnits("$s ft");

$image_1 = createLaTeXImage();
$image_1->addToPreamble(latexImagePreamble());
$image_1->BEGIN_LATEX_IMAGE
\begin{tikzpicture}
  \draw[fill=wood] (0,0) -| (5,3) -| cycle;
  \draw[fill=lightemerald] (0.5,0.5) -| (4.5,2.5) -| cycle;
  \draw[dashed] (2.5,0) -- node[pos=0.5, right] {\(x\)} (2.5,0.5);
  \draw[dashed] (0,1.5) -- node[pos=0.5, above] {\(x\)} (0.5,1.5);
  \node[above] at (2.5,0.5) {\($w\) ft};
  \node[above, rotate=-90] at (0.5,1.5) {\($h\) ft};
\end{tikzpicture}

END_LATEX_IMAGE

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
A vegetable garden will be surrounded by a frame of grass sod. The garden itself will be [`[$wU]`] by [`[$hU]\text{.}`] The widths of the four edges of the frame will be equal to each other. There is only [`[$areaU]`] of grass sod available, and it will all be used for this frame. How wide should the four edges be? (What is the value of [`x`] in the diagram?)

>> [@image(insertGraph($image_1), width=>240)@]*  <<

[_]{$sU}{20}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can find a formula for the surface area of the frame by taking the area of the outer rectangle and subtracting the area of the inner rectangle. The outer rectangle's width is [`[$w]+2x`] feet. Its height is [`[$h]+2x`] feet. So its area is [`([$w]+2x)([$h]+2x)`] square feet. The inner rectangle area is [`([$w])([$h])`] square feet. So the surface area of the frame, in square feet, is [`([$w]+2x)([$h]+2x)-([$w])([$h])\text{,}`] which simplifies to [`[$surface]\text{.}`] So we must solve the equation [`[$surface]=[$area]\text{.}`]

Writing the quadratic equation in standard form, [`[$f]=0\text{.}`] Now we apply the quadratic formula.

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
x\amp=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\\
\amp=\frac{[$negb]\pm\sqrt{[$bsquared]-4([$a])([$c])}}{2([$a])}\\
\amp=\frac{[$negb]\pm\sqrt{[$discriminant]}}{[$a2]}\\
\amp\approx\frac{[$negb]\pm[$sqrtdisc]}{[$a2]}\\
x\approx\amp\frac{[$negb]-[$sqrtdisc]}{[$a2]}\quad\text{or}\quad x\approx\frac{[$negb]+[$sqrtdisc]}{[$a2]}\\
x\approx\amp[$r]\quad\text{or}\quad x\approx[$s]
\end{aligned}
```]

The possible solutions are [`[$r]`] and [`[$s]\text{,}`] but only [`[$s]`] makes sense in this context. Each edge of the frame will be about [`[$sU]`] wide.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

